habitat_description:
Its range includes north Ontario (Big Bear Lake in northwest Canada) then continues into Utah, North New Mexico; from north Wisconsin to Nebraska, Missouri, northern New York, northern Arkansas, northwestern Vermont, and northern Oklahoma; some localities been reported in northeast New Mexico where it borders with Arizona, others in southeast Colorado (Conant and Collins 1998; Lemmon et al. 2007). The habitat as marshy, this species is found in far-northern ponds, meadows, and lakes; some populations found in similar environments found in mountainous habitats (P. triseriata maculata Conant and Collins 1998).

Elevational range extends to above 3,670 meters in Colorado and Utah (Hammerson 1999, Stebbins 2003).
